    public static interface StrictPriorityQueue.MergeOperation<E>
    The merge operation two perform on two equally-ranked elements.
    Author:
    Malte Isberner

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      E merge(E oldObject, E newObject)
      Merges the old element and the new element into a replacement element.

    • Method Detail

      • merge

        E merge(E oldObject,
        E newObject)
        Merges the old element and the new element into a replacement element.

        Implementations can assume that cmp.compare(oldObject, newObject) == 0 holds for the comparator cmp specified in StrictPriorityQueue.StrictPriorityQueue(Comparator, MergeOperation). In turn, they must guarantee that also cmp.compare(result, oldObject) == 0 holds for the return value result.

        Parameters:
        oldObject - the old element
        newObject - the new element
        Returns:
        the replacement element
